1/* packet-isakmp.c
2 * Routines for the Internet Security Association and Key Management Protocol
3 * (ISAKMP) (RFC 2408) and the Internet IP Security Domain of Interpretation
4 * for ISAKMP (RFC 2407)
5 * Brad Robel-Forrest <brad.robel-forrest@watchguard.com>
6 *
7 * Added routines for the Internet Key Exchange (IKEv2) Protocol
8 * (draft-ietf-ipsec-ikev2-17.txt)
9 * Shoichi Sakane <sakane@tanu.org>
10 *
11 * Added routines for RFC3947 Negotiation of NAT-Traversal in the IKE
12 * ronnie sahlberg
13 *
14 * 04/2009 Added routines for decryption of IKEv2 Encrypted Payload
15 * Naoyoshi Ueda <piyomaru3141@gmail.com>
16 *
17 * Wireshark - Network traffic analyzer
18 * By Gerald Combs <gerald@wireshark.org>
19 * Copyright 1998 Gerald Combs
20 *
21 * This program is free software; you can redistribute it and/or
22 * modify it under the terms of the GNU General Public License
23 * as published by the Free Software Foundation; either version 2
24 * of the License, or (at your option) any later version.
25 *
26 * This program is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
27 * but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
28 * MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. See the
29 * GNU General Public License for more details.
30 *
31 * You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License
32 * along with this program; if not, write to the Free Software
33 * Foundation, Inc., 51 Franklin Street, Fifth Floor, Boston, MA 02110-1301 USA.
34 *
35 * References:
36 * IKEv2 http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4306.txt?number=4306
37 * IKEv2bis http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5996.txt?number=5996
38 *
39 * http://www.iana.org/assignments/isakmp-registry (last updated 2011-11-07)
40 * http://www.iana.org/assignments/ipsec-registry (last updated 2011-03-14)
41 * http://www.iana.org/assignments/ikev2-parameters (last updated 2011-12-19)
42 */

1756static ikev2_encr_alg_spec_t* ikev2_decrypt_find_encr_spec(guint num) {
1757 ikev2_encr_alg_spec_t *e;
1758
1759 for (e = ikev2_encr_algs; e->number != 0; e++) {
1760 if (e->number == num) {
1761 return e;
1762 }
1763 }
1764 return NULL((void*)0);
1765}
1766
1767static ikev2_auth_alg_spec_t* ikev2_decrypt_find_auth_spec(guint num) {
1768 ikev2_auth_alg_spec_t *a;
1769
1770 for (a = ikev2_auth_algs; a->number != 0; a++) {
1771 if (a->number == num) {
1772 return a;
1773 }
1774 }
1775 return NULL((void*)0);
1776}
1777
1778static gint ikev1_find_gcry_cipher_algo(guint ike_cipher, guint ike_keylen) {
1779 switch(ike_cipher) {
1780 case ENC_3DES_CBC5:
1781 return GCRY_CIPHER_3DES;
1782
1783 case ENC_DES_CBC1:
1784 return GCRY_CIPHER_DES;
1785
1786 case ENC_AES_CBC7:
1787 switch (ike_keylen) {
1788 case 128:
1789 return GCRY_CIPHER_AES128GCRY_CIPHER_AES;
1790 case 192:
1791 return GCRY_CIPHER_AES192;
1792 case 256:
1793 return GCRY_CIPHER_AES256;
1794 }
1795 return GCRY_CIPHER_NONE;
1796 }
1797 return GCRY_CIPHER_NONE;
1798}
1799
1800static gint ikev1_find_gcry_md_algo(guint ike_hash) {
1801 switch(ike_hash) {
1802 case HMAC_MD51:
1803 return GCRY_MD_MD5;
1804 case HMAC_SHA2:
1805 return GCRY_MD_SHA1;
1806 case HMAC_SHA2_2564:
1807 return GCRY_MD_SHA256;
1808 case HMAC_SHA2_3845:
1809 return GCRY_MD_SHA384;
1810 case HMAC_SHA2_5126:
1811 return GCRY_MD_SHA512;
1812 }
1813 return GCRY_MD_NONE;
1814}
1815
1816static gpointer
1817generate_iv(const gpointer b1, gsize b1_len,
1818 const gpointer b2, gsize b2_len,
1819 gint md_algo, gsize iv_len) {
1820
1821 gcry_md_hd_t md_ctx;
1822 gpointer iv;
1823
1824 if (gcry_md_open(&md_ctx, md_algo, 0) != GPG_ERR_NO_ERROR)
1825 return NULL((void*)0);
1826
1827 gcry_md_write(md_ctx, b1, b1_len);
1828 gcry_md_write(md_ctx, b2, b2_len);
1829
1830 iv = wmem_alloc(wmem_file_scope(), iv_len);
1831 memcpy(iv, gcry_md_read(md_ctx, md_algo), iv_len);
1832 gcry_md_close(md_ctx);
1833
1834 return iv;
1835}
1836
1837/* Get the IV previously stored for the current message ID,
1838 * or create a new IV if the message ID was not seen before.
1839 * The caller owns the result and does not need to copy it.
1840 * This function may return NULL.
1841 */
1842static gpointer
1843get_iv(guint32 message_id, decrypt_data_t *decr) {
1844 gpointer iv, iv1;
1845 gsize cipher_blklen;
1846 gpointer msgid_key;
1847 guint32 msgid_net;
1848 gboolean found;
1849
1850 cipher_blklen = decr->cipher_blklen;
1851
1852 /* Get the current IV for the given message ID,
1853 * and remove it from the hash table without destroying it. */
1854 msgid_key = GINT_TO_POINTER(message_id)((gpointer) (glong) (message_id));
1855 found = g_hash_table_lookup_extended(decr->iv_hash, msgid_key, NULL((void*)0), &iv);
1856 if (found) {
1857 g_hash_table_steal(decr->iv_hash, msgid_key);
1858 return iv;
1859 }
1860
1861 /* No IV for this message ID was found; a new phase has started.
1862 * Generate the first IV for it from its message ID and the current
1863 * phase 1 IV. The phase 1 IV always exists in the hash table
1864 * and is not NULL.
1865 */
1866 iv1 = g_hash_table_lookup(decr->iv_hash, GINT_TO_POINTER(0)((gpointer) (glong) (0)));
1867 msgid_net = g_htonl(message_id)((((__extension__ ({ guint32 __v, __x = ((guint32) (message_id
)); if (__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = ((guint32) ( (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x000000ffU) << 24) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x0000ff00U) << 8) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x00ff0000U) >> 8) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0xff000000U) >> 24))); else __asm__
("bswapl %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0" (__x)); __v; })))));
1868 iv = generate_iv(iv1, cipher_blklen,
1869 &msgid_net, sizeof(msgid_net),
1870 decr->digest_algo, cipher_blklen);
1871 return iv;
1872}
1873
1874/* Fill in the next IV from the final ciphertext block. */
1875static void
1876set_next_iv(const guint8 *buf, guint buf_len, guint32 message_id, decrypt_data_t *decr) {
1877 gpointer iv;
1878 gsize cipher_blklen;
1879 gpointer msgid_key;
1880
1881 cipher_blklen = decr->cipher_blklen;
1882
1883 if (buf_len < cipher_blklen) {
1884 iv = NULL((void*)0);
1885 } else {
1886 iv = wmem_alloc(wmem_file_scope(), cipher_blklen);
1887 memcpy(iv, buf + buf_len - cipher_blklen, cipher_blklen);
1888 }
1889
1890 msgid_key = GINT_TO_POINTER(message_id)((gpointer) (glong) (message_id));
1891 g_hash_table_insert(decr->iv_hash, msgid_key, iv);
1892}
1893
1894static void
1895update_ivs(packet_info *pinfo, const guint8 *buf, guint buf_len, guint32 message_id, decrypt_data_t *decr) {
1896 gpointer iv;
1897
1898 /* Get the current IV and store it as per-packet data. */
1899 iv = get_iv(message_id, decr);
1900 p_add_proto_data(wmem_file_scope(), pinfo, proto_isakmp, PINFO_CBC_IV1, iv);
1901
1902 set_next_iv(buf, buf_len, message_id, decr);
1903}
1904
1905static gboolean
1906prepare_decrypt_params(decrypt_data_t *decr) {
1907 decr->cipher_algo = ikev1_find_gcry_cipher_algo(decr->ike_encr_alg,
1908 decr->ike_encr_keylen);
1909 decr->digest_algo = ikev1_find_gcry_md_algo(decr->ike_hash_alg);
1910
1911 if (decr->cipher_algo == GCRY_CIPHER_NONE ||
1912 decr->digest_algo == GCRY_MD_NONE)
1913 return FALSE(0);
1914
1915 decr->cipher_keylen = gcry_cipher_get_algo_keylen(decr->cipher_algo);
1916 decr->cipher_blklen = gcry_cipher_get_algo_blklen(decr->cipher_algo);
1917 decr->digest_len = gcry_md_get_algo_dlen(decr->digest_algo);
1918
1919 if (decr->secret_len < decr->cipher_keylen ||
1920 decr->digest_len < decr->cipher_blklen)
1921 return FALSE(0);
1922
1923 if (decr->gi_len == 0 || decr->gr_len == 0)
1924 return FALSE(0);
1925
1926 return TRUE(!(0));
1927}
1928
1929/* Generate phase 1 IV from DH values
1930 * and store it into the IV hash table. */
1931static gboolean
1932prepare_phase1_iv(decrypt_data_t *decr) {
1933 gpointer iv;
1934
1935 iv = generate_iv(decr->gi, decr->gi_len,
1936 decr->gr, decr->gr_len,
1937 decr->digest_algo, decr->cipher_blklen);
1938 if (!iv)
1939 return FALSE(0);
1940
1941 g_hash_table_insert(decr->iv_hash, GINT_TO_POINTER(0)((gpointer) (glong) (0)), iv);
1942 return TRUE(!(0));
1943}
1944
1945static gboolean
1946prepare_decrypt(decrypt_data_t *decr) {
1947 gboolean result;
1948
1949 if (!decr)
1950 return FALSE(0);
1951
1952 if (decr->state == DECR_PARAMS_INIT0) {
1953 /* Short-circuit evaluation is intended. */
1954 result = prepare_decrypt_params(decr) &&
1955 prepare_phase1_iv(decr);
1956 decr->state = result ? DECR_PARAMS_READY1 : DECR_PARAMS_FAIL2;
1957 }
1958
1959 return (decr->state == DECR_PARAMS_READY1);
1960}
1961
1962static decrypt_data_t *
1963create_decrypt_data(void) {
1964 decrypt_data_t *decr;
1965
1966 decr = (decrypt_data_t *)g_slice_alloc(sizeof(decrypt_data_t));
1967 memset(decr, 0, sizeof(decrypt_data_t));
1968 decr->iv_hash = g_hash_table_new(NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
1969 clear_address(&decr->initiator);
1970
1971 return decr;
1972}
1973
1974static tvbuff_t *
1975decrypt_payload(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, const guint8 *buf, guint buf_len, decrypt_data_t *decr) {
1976 guint8 *decrypted_data;
1977 gcry_cipher_hd_t decr_ctx;
1978 tvbuff_t *encr_tvb;
1979 gpointer iv;
1980 gboolean error;
1981
1982 if (buf_len < decr->cipher_blklen)
1983 return NULL((void*)0);
1984
1985 iv = p_get_proto_data(wmem_file_scope(), pinfo, proto_isakmp, PINFO_CBC_IV1);
1986 if (!iv)
1987 return NULL((void*)0);
1988
1989 if (gcry_cipher_open(&decr_ctx, decr->cipher_algo, GCRY_CIPHER_MODE_CBC, 0) != GPG_ERR_NO_ERROR)
1990 return NULL((void*)0);
1991
1992 decrypted_data = (guint8 *)wmem_alloc(pinfo->pool, buf_len);
1993
1994 /* Short-circuit evaluation is intended. */
1995 error = gcry_cipher_setiv(decr_ctx, iv, decr->cipher_blklen) ||
1996 gcry_cipher_setkey(decr_ctx, decr->secret, decr->secret_len) ||
1997 gcry_cipher_decrypt(decr_ctx, decrypted_data, buf_len, buf, buf_len);
1998
1999 gcry_cipher_close(decr_ctx);
2000 if (error)
2001 return NULL((void*)0);
2002
2003 encr_tvb = tvb_new_child_real_data(tvb, decrypted_data, buf_len, buf_len);
2004
2005 /* Add the decrypted data to the data source list. */
2006 add_new_data_source(pinfo, encr_tvb, "Decrypted IKE");
2007
2008 return encr_tvb;
2009}

2011#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */

2715/* Tries to match val against each element in the value_string array vs.
2716 Returns the associated string ptr, and sets "*idx" to the index in
2717 that table, on a match, and returns NULL, and sets "*idx" to -1,
2718 on failure. */
2719static const gchar*
2720match_strbyte_idx(const guint8 *val, const gint val_len, const byte_string *vs, gint *idx) {
2721 gint i = 0;
2722
2723 if (vs) {
2724 while (vs[i].strptr) {
2725 if (val_len >= vs[i].len && !memcmp(vs[i].value, val, vs[i].len)) {
2726 *idx = i;
2727 return(vs[i].strptr);
2728 }
2729 i++;
2730 }
2731 }
2732
2733 *idx = -1;
2734 return NULL((void*)0);
2735}
2736/* Like match_strbyte_idx(), but doesn't return the index. */
2737static const gchar*
2738match_strbyte(const guint8 *val,const gint val_len, const byte_string *vs) {
2739 gint ignore_me;
2740 return match_strbyte_idx(val, val_len, vs, &ignore_me);
2741}
2742
2743/* Tries to match val against each element in the value_string array vs.
2744 Returns the associated string ptr on a match.
2745 Formats val with fmt, and returns the resulting string, on failure. */
2746static const gchar*
2747byte_to_str(const guint8 *val,const gint val_len, const byte_string *vs, const char *fmt) {
2748 const gchar *ret;
2749
2750 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(fmt != NULL)((void) ((fmt != ((void*)0)) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug
(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\""
, "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-isakmp.c"
, 2750, "fmt != ((void*)0)")))));
2751 ret = match_strbyte(val, val_len, vs);
2752 if (ret != NULL((void*)0))
2753 return ret;
2754
2755 return wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(), fmt, val);
2756}

2866 dissect_ikev2_fragmentation(tvb, offset + 4, ntree, pinfo, message_id, next_payload, is_request, decr_data );

2872 }
2873 }

2875 proto_tree_add_expert_format(ntree, pinfo, &ei_isakmp_payload_bad_length, tvb, 0, 0,
2876 "Payload (bogus, length is %u, greater than remaining length %d",
2877 payload_length, length);
2878 return;
2879 }
2880 else {
2881 proto_tree_add_expert_format(ntree, pinfo, &ei_isakmp_payload_bad_length, tvb, 0, 0,
2882 "Payload (bogus, length is %u, must be at least 4)",
2883 payload_length);
2884 payload_length = 4;
2885 }
2886
2887 offset += payload_length;
2888 length -= payload_length;
2889 }

3328/* Dissect life duration, which is variable-length. Note that this function
3329 * handles both/either the security association life duration as defined in
3330 * section 4.5 of RFC2407 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2407), as well as the
3331 * life duration according to the attribute classes table in Appendix A of
3332 * RFC2409: http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2409#page-33 */
3333static void
3334dissect_life_duration(tvbuff_t *tvb, proto_tree *tree, proto_item *ti, int hf_uint32, int hf_uint64, int hf_bytes, int offset, guint len)

3338 break;

3353 break;

3361 break;
3362 }
3363 case 4: {
3364 guint32 val;
3365 val = tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset);
3366
3367 proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(tree, hf_uint32, tvb, offset, len, val, "%u", val);

4037 length -= 4;
4038
4039 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_auth_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4040
4041}

4060
4061static void
4062dissect_cisco_fragmentation(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree, packet_info *pinfo)
4063{
4064 guint8 seq; /* Packet sequence number, starting from 1 */
4065 guint8 last;
4066 proto_tree *ptree;
4067 ptree = proto_tree_get_parent(tree);
4068 if (length < 4)
4069 return;
4070
4071 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_cisco_frag_packetid, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4072 offset += 2;
4073 seq = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4074 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_cisco_frag_seq, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4075 offset += 1;
4076 last = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4077 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_cisco_frag_last, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4078 offset += 1;
4079 /*length-=4;*/
4080
4081 /* Start Reassembly stuff for Cisco IKE fragmentation */
4082 {
4083 gboolean save_fragmented;
4084 tvbuff_t *defrag_isakmp_tvb;
4085 fragment_head *frag_msg;
4086
4087 save_fragmented = pinfo->fragmented;
4088 pinfo->fragmented = TRUE(!(0));
4089 frag_msg = fragment_add_seq_check(&isakmp_cisco_reassembly_table, tvb, offset,
4090 pinfo,
4091 12345, /*FIXME: Fragmented packet id, guint16, somehow get CKY here */
4092 NULL((void*)0),
4093 seq-1, /* fragment sequence number, starting from 0 */
4094 tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset), /* fragment length - to the end */
4095 !last); /* More fragments? */
4096 defrag_isakmp_tvb = process_reassembled_data(tvb, offset, pinfo,
4097 "Reassembled ISAKMP", frag_msg,
4098 &isakmp_frag_items, /* groups and items, using same as Cisco */
4099 NULL((void*)0), ptree);
4100
4101 if (last && defrag_isakmp_tvb) { /* take it all */
4102 dissect_isakmp(defrag_isakmp_tvb, pinfo, ptree, NULL((void*)0));
4103 }
4104 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO,
4105 " (%sMessage fragment %u%s)",
4106 (last && frag_msg ? "Reassembled + " : ""),
4107 seq, (last ? " - last" : ""));
4108 pinfo->fragmented = save_fragmented;
4109 }
4110 /* End Reassembly stuff for Cisco IKE fragmentation */
4111
4112}
4113
4114/* This is RFC7383 reassembly. */
4115static void
4116dissect_ikev2_fragmentation(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, proto_tree *tree,
4117#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
4118 packet_info *pinfo, guint message_id, guint8 next_payload, gboolean is_request, void* decr_info)
4119#else
4120 packet_info *pinfo, guint message_id, guint8 next_payload, gboolean is_request _U___attribute__((unused)), void* decr_info _U___attribute__((unused)))
4121#endif
4122{
4123 guint16 fragment_number, total_fragments;
4124#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
4125 gboolean message_next_payload_set = FALSE(0);
4126 guint8 message_next_payload = 0;
4127 gint iv_len, icd_len;
4128 gint iv_offset;
4129 gint icd_offset;
4130 ikev2_decrypt_data_t *key_info;
4131#endif
4132
4133 /* Fragment Number */
4134 fragment_number = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset);
4135 total_fragments = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset+2);
4136 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ike2_fragment_number, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4137 offset += 2;
4138 if (fragment_number == 0) {
4139 proto_tree_add_expert_format(tree, pinfo, &ei_isakmp_bad_fragment_number, tvb, 0, 0,
4140 "Fragment number must not be zero");
4141 }
4142 else if (fragment_number > total_fragments) {
4143 proto_tree_add_expert_format(tree, pinfo, &ei_isakmp_bad_fragment_number, tvb, 0, 0,
4144 "Fragment number (%u) must not be greater than total fragments (%u)",
4145 fragment_number, total_fragments);
4146 }
4147
4148 /* During the first pass, store in the conversation the next_payload */
4149 if (!pinfo->fd->flags.visited && (fragment_number == 1)) {
4150 /* Create/update conversation with message_id -> next_payload */
4151 conversation_t* p_conv = find_or_create_conversation(pinfo);
4152 ikev2_fragmentation_state_t *p_state = wmem_new0(wmem_file_scope(), ikev2_fragmentation_state_t)((ikev2_fragmentation_state_t*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_file_scope()
), sizeof(ikev2_fragmentation_state_t)));
4153 p_state->message_id = message_id;
4154 p_state->next_payload = next_payload;
4155
4156 /* Store the state with the conversation */
4157 conversation_add_proto_data(p_conv, proto_isakmp, (void*)p_state);
4158 }
4159
4160 /* Total fragments */
4161 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ike2_total_fragments, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4162 if (total_fragments == 0) {
4163 proto_tree_add_expert_format(tree, pinfo, &ei_isakmp_bad_fragment_number, tvb, 0, 0,
4164 "Total fragments must not be zero");
4165 }
4166
4167 /* Show fragment summary in Info column */
4168 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " (fragment %u/%u)", fragment_number, total_fragments);
4169
4170#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
4171 offset += 2;
4172
4173 /* If this is the last fragment, need to know what the payload type for the reassembled message is,
4174 which was included in the first fragment */
4175 if (fragment_number == total_fragments) {
4176 if (!pinfo->fd->flags.visited) {
4177 /* On first pass, get it from the conversation info */
4178 conversation_t *p_conv = find_conversation(pinfo->num, &pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst,
4179 pinfo->ptype, pinfo->srcport,
4180 pinfo->destport, 0);
4181 if (p_conv != NULL((void*)0)) {
4182 ikev2_fragmentation_state_t *p_state = (ikev2_fragmentation_state_t*)conversation_get_proto_data(p_conv, proto_isakmp);
4183 if (p_state != NULL((void*)0)) {
4184 if (p_state->message_id == message_id) {
4185 message_next_payload = p_state->next_payload;
4186 message_next_payload_set = TRUE(!(0));
4187
4188 /* Store in table for this frame for future passes */
4189 g_hash_table_insert(defrag_next_payload_hash, GUINT_TO_POINTER(pinfo->num)((gpointer) (gulong) (pinfo->num)), GUINT_TO_POINTER((guint)message_next_payload)((gpointer) (gulong) ((guint)message_next_payload)));
4190 }
4191 }
4192 }
4193 }
4194 else {
4195 /* On later passes, look up in hash table by frame number */
4196 message_next_payload = (guint8)GPOINTER_TO_UINT(g_hash_table_lookup(defrag_next_payload_hash, GUINT_TO_POINTER(pinfo->num)))((guint) (gulong) (g_hash_table_lookup(defrag_next_payload_hash
, ((gpointer) (gulong) (pinfo->num)))));
4197 if (message_next_payload != 0) {
4198 message_next_payload_set = TRUE(!(0));
4199 }
4200 }
4201 }
4202
4203 /* Can only know lengths of following fields if we have the key information */
4204 if (decr_info) {
4205 key_info = (ikev2_decrypt_data_t*)(decr_info);
4206 iv_len = key_info->encr_spec->iv_len;
4207 icd_len = key_info->auth_spec->trunc_len;
4208 }
4209 else {
4210 /* Can't show any more info. */
4211 return;
4212 }
4213
4214 /* Initialization Vector */
4215 iv_offset = offset;
4216 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_enc_iv, tvb, offset, iv_len, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4217 offset += iv_len;
4218
4219 icd_offset = offset + tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset) - icd_len;
4220
4221 /* Encryption data */
4222 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_enc_data, tvb, offset, icd_offset-offset, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4223
4224 /* Can only check how much padding there is after decrypting... */
4225
4226 /* Start Reassembly stuff for IKE2 fragmentation */
4227 {
4228 gboolean save_fragmented;
4229 tvbuff_t *defrag_decrypted_isakmp_tvb;
4230 tvbuff_t *isakmp_decrypted_fragment_tvb;
4231 fragment_head *frag_msg;
4232 guint8 padding_length;
4233 guint16 fragment_length;
4234
4235 /* Decrypt but don't dissect this encrypted payload. */
4236 isakmp_decrypted_fragment_tvb = dissect_enc(tvb, iv_offset, tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, iv_offset), tree, pinfo,
4237 0, /* Payload type won't be used in this call, and may not know yet */
4238 is_request,
4239 decr_info,
4240 FALSE(0) /* Don't dissect decrypted tvb as not a completed payload */
4241 );
4242
4243 /* Save pinfo->fragmented, will later restore it */
4244 save_fragmented = pinfo->fragmented;
4245 pinfo->fragmented = TRUE(!(0));
4246
4247 /* Remove padding length + any padding bytes from reassembled payload */
4248 padding_length = tvb_get_guint8(isakmp_decrypted_fragment_tvb, tvb_reported_length(isakmp_decrypted_fragment_tvb)-1);
4249 fragment_length = tvb_reported_length(isakmp_decrypted_fragment_tvb) - 1 - padding_length;
4250
4251 /* Adding decrypted tvb into reassembly table here */
4252 frag_msg = fragment_add_seq_check(&isakmp_ike2_reassembly_table,
4253 isakmp_decrypted_fragment_tvb,
4254 0, /* offset */
4255 pinfo,
4256 message_id, /* message_id from top-level header */
4257 NULL((void*)0), /* data? */
4258 fragment_number-1, /* fragment sequence number, starting from 0 */
4259 fragment_length, /* fragment - (padding_length + padding) */
4260 fragment_number < total_fragments); /* More fragments? */
4261
4262 defrag_decrypted_isakmp_tvb = process_reassembled_data(tvb, offset, pinfo,
4263 "Reassembled IKE2 ISAKMP",
4264 frag_msg,
4265 &isakmp_frag_items, /* Tree IDs & items - using same ones as Cisco. */
4266 NULL((void*)0), tree);
4267
4268 if (defrag_decrypted_isakmp_tvb && key_info && message_next_payload_set) {
4269 /* Completely reassembled - already decrypted - dissect reassembled payload if know next payload type */
4270 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " (reassembled)");
4271 dissect_payloads(defrag_decrypted_isakmp_tvb, tree,
4272 2, /* Could store with next_payload, but wouldn't be here otherwise.. */
4273 message_next_payload,
4274 0, tvb_reported_length(defrag_decrypted_isakmp_tvb),
4275 pinfo, message_id, is_request, decr_info);
4276 }
4277 /* Restore this flag */
4278 pinfo->fragmented = save_fragmented;
4279 }
4280 /* End Reassembly stuff for IKE2 fragmentation */
4281#endif
4282}
4283
4284
4285static void
4286dissect_notif(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree, int isakmp_version)
4287{
4288 guint8 spi_size;
4289 guint16 msgtype;
4290 int offset_end = 0;
4291 offset_end = offset + length;
4292
4293 if (isakmp_version == 1) {
4294 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_doi, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4295 offset += 4;
4296 length -= 4;
4297 }
4298
4299 if (isakmp_version == 1)
4300 {
4301 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_protoid_v1, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4302 }else if (isakmp_version == 2)
4303 {
4304 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_protoid_v2, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4305 }
4306 offset += 1;
4307 length -= 1;
4308
4309 spi_size = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4310 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_spisize, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4311 offset += 1;
4312 length -= 1;
4313
4314 msgtype = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset);
4315
4316 if (isakmp_version == 1)
4317 {
4318 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_msgtype_v1, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4319 }else if (isakmp_version == 2)
4320 {
4321 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_msgtype_v2, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4322 proto_item_append_text(tree, " - %s",
4323 rval_to_str_const(tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset),
4324 notifmsg_v2_type,
4325 "Unknown"));
4326 }
4327 offset += 2;
4328 length -= 2;
4329
4330 if (spi_size) {
4331 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_spi, tvb, offset, spi_size, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4332 offset += spi_size;
4333 length -= spi_size;
4334 }
4335
4336 /* Notification Data */
4337
4338 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4339
4340 if (isakmp_version == 1)
4341 {
4342 switch (msgtype) {
4343 case 36136: /* DPD ARE YOU THERE */
4344 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_dpd_are_you_there, tvb, offset, length, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4345 break;
4346 case 36137: /* DPD ARE YOU THERE ACK */
4347 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_dpd_are_you_there_ack, tvb, offset, length, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4348 break;
4349 case 40501: /* UNITY Load Balance */
4350 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_unity_load_balance, tvb, offset, length, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4351 break;
4352 default:
4353 /* No Default Action */
4354 break;
4355 }
4356
4357 } else if (isakmp_version == 2)
4358 {
4359 switch(msgtype){
4360 case 16387: /* IPCOMP_SUPPORTED */
4361 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ipcomp_cpi, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4362 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ipcomp_transform_id, tvb, offset+2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4363 break;
4364 case 16407: /* REDIRECT */
4365 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_gw_ident_type, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4366 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_gw_ident_len, tvb, offset+1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4367 switch(tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset)){ /* Ident Type ? */
4368 case 1:
4369 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_new_resp_gw_ident_ipv4, tvb, offset+2, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4370 break;
4371 case 2:
4372 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_new_resp_gw_ident_ipv6, tvb, offset+2, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4373 break;
4374 case 3:
4375 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_new_resp_gw_ident_fqdn, tvb, offset+2, tvb_get_guint8(tvb,offset+1), ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000);
4376 break;
4377 default :
4378 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_new_resp_gw_ident, tvb, offset+2, tvb_get_guint8(tvb,offset+1), ENC_NA0x00000000);
4379 break;
4380 }
4381 length -= tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset+1) + 2;
4382 offset += tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset+1) + 2;
4383 if(length)
4384 {
4385 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_nonce_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4386 }
4387 break;
4388 case 16408: /* REDIRECT_FROM */
4389 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_gw_ident_type, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4390 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_gw_ident_len, tvb, offset+1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4391 switch(tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset)){ /* Ident Type ? */
4392 case 1:
4393 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_org_resp_gw_ident_ipv4, tvb, offset+2, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4394 break;
4395 case 2:
4396 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_org_resp_gw_ident_ipv6, tvb, offset+2, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4397 break;
4398 default :
4399 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_redirect_org_resp_gw_ident, tvb, offset+2, tvb_get_guint8(tvb,offset+1), ENC_NA0x00000000);
4400 break;
4401 }
4402 break;
4403 case 16409: /* TICKET_LT_OPAQUE */
4404 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ticket_lifetime, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4405 offset += 4;
4406 length -= 4;
4407 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ticket_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4408 break;
4409 case 16413: /* TICKET_OPAQUE */
4410 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ticket_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4411 break;
4412 case 16416: /* ROHC_SUPPORTED */
4413 while (offset < offset_end) {
4414 offset += dissect_rohc_supported(tvb, pinfo, tree, offset);
4415 }
4416 break;
4417 case 16419: /* QUICK_CRASH_DETECTION */
4418 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_qcd_token_secret_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4419 break;
4420 case 16422: /* IKEV2_MESSAGE_ID_SYNC */
4421 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ha_nonce_data, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4422 offset += 4;
4423 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ha_expected_send_req_msg_id, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4424 offset += 4;
4425 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ha_expected_recv_req_msg_id, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4426 break;
4427 case 16423: /* IPSEC_REPLAY_COUNTER_SYNC */
4428 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_ha_incoming_ipsec_sa_delta_value, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4429 break;
4430 case 16424: /* SECURE_PASSWORD_METHODS */
4431 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_notify_data_secure_password_methods, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4432 break;
4433 default:
4434 /* No Default Action */
4435 break;
4436 }
4437 }
4438}
4439
4440static void
4441dissect_delete(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree, int isakmp_version)
4442{
4443 guint8 spi_size;
4444
4445 if (isakmp_version == 1) {
4446 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_delete_doi, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4447 offset += 4;
4448 length -= 4;
4449 }
4450
4451
4452 if (isakmp_version == 1)
4453 {
4454 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_delete_protoid_v1, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4455 }else if (isakmp_version == 2)
4456 {
4457 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_delete_protoid_v2, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4458 }
4459
4460 offset += 1;
4461 length -= 1;
4462
4463 spi_size = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4464 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_spisize, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4465 offset += 1;
4466 length -= 1;
4467
4468 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_num_spis, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4469 offset += 2;
4470 length -= 2;
4471
4472 if (spi_size > 0) {
4473 while (length > 0) {
4474 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_delete_spi, tvb, offset, spi_size, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4475 offset+=spi_size;
4476 length-=spi_size;
4477 }
4478 }
4479}

4481
4482static int
4483dissect_vid(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree)
4484{
4485 const guint8 * pVID;
4486 const char * vendorstring;
4487
4488 pVID = tvb_get_ptr(tvb, offset, length);
4489
4490 vendorstring = byte_to_str(pVID, (gint)length, vendor_id, "Unknown Vendor ID");
4491 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_bytes, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4492 proto_tree_add_string(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_string, tvb, offset, length, vendorstring);
4493 proto_item_append_text(tree," : %s", vendorstring);
4494
4495 /* very old CryptPro/GOST (Check Point R65) VID */
4496 if (length >= 24 && memcmp(pVID, VID_CP_01_R65, 20) == 0)
4497 {
4498 offset += 20;
4499 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_cp_product, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4500 offset +=4;
4501 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_cp_version, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4502 offset +=4;
4503 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_cp_timestamp, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4504 offset +=4;
4505 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_cp_reserved, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4506 offset +=4;
4507 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_cp_features, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4508 offset +=4;
4509 }
4510
4511 /* Cisco Unity VID */
4512 if (length >= 14 && memcmp(pVID, VID_CISCO_UNITY, 14) == 0)
4513 {
4514 offset += 14;
4515 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_cisco_unity_major, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4516 proto_item_append_text(tree, " %u", tvb_get_guint8(tvb,offset));
4517 offset += 1;
4518 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_cisco_unity_minor, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4519 proto_item_append_text(tree, ".%u", tvb_get_guint8(tvb,offset));
4520 offset += 1;
4521 }
4522
4523 /* VID_MS_NT5_ISAKMPOAKLEY */
4524 if (length >= 16 && memcmp(pVID, VID_MS_NT5_ISAKMPOAKLEY, 16) == 0)
4525 {
4526 offset += 16;
4527 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_ms_nt5_isakmpoakley, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4528 offset += 4;
4529 }
4530
4531 /* VID_ARUBA_VIA_AUTH_PROFILE */
4532 if (length >= 19 && memcmp(pVID, VID_ARUBA_VIA_AUTH_PROFILE, 19) == 0)
4533 {
4534 offset += 19;
4535 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_vid_aruba_via_auth_profile, tvb, offset, length-19, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000);
4536 offset += 4;
4537 }
4538 return offset;
4539}
4540/* Returns the number of bytes consumed by this option. */
4541static int
4542dissect_config_attribute(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *cfg_attr_type_tree, int offset, int isakmp_version, gboolean is_request)
4543{
4544 guint optlen, cfg_attr_type, len = 0;
4545 proto_item *cfg_attr_type_item = NULL((void*)0);
4546 proto_tree *sub_cfg_attr_type_tree = NULL((void*)0);
4547 guint i;
4548 const guint8* str;
4549
4550 cfg_attr_type = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset);
4551 optlen = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset+2);
4552 len = 2;
4553
4554 /* No Length ? */
4555 if (cfg_attr_type & 0x8000) {
4556 cfg_attr_type = cfg_attr_type & 0x7fff;
4557 len = 0;
4558 optlen = 2;
4559 }
4560
4561 if (isakmp_version == 1) {
4562 cfg_attr_type_item = proto_tree_add_none_format(cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr, tvb, offset, 2+len+optlen, "Attribute Type: (t=%d,l=%d) %s", cfg_attr_type, optlen, rval_to_str(cfg_attr_type,vs_v1_cfgattr,"Unknown Attribute Type (%02d)") );
4563 sub_cfg_attr_type_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(cfg_attr_type_item, ett_isakmp_cfg_attr);
4564 proto_tree_add_uint(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_type_v1, tvb, offset, 2, cfg_attr_type);
4565 } else if (isakmp_version == 2) {
4566 cfg_attr_type_item = proto_tree_add_none_format(cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr, tvb, offset, 2+len+optlen, "Attribute Type: (t=%d,l=%d) %s", cfg_attr_type, optlen, rval_to_str(cfg_attr_type,vs_v2_cfgattr,"Unknown Attribute Type (%02d)") );
4567 sub_cfg_attr_type_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(cfg_attr_type_item, ett_isakmp_cfg_attr);
4568 proto_tree_add_uint(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_type_v2, tvb, offset, 2, cfg_attr_type);
4569 }
4570 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_format, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4571 offset += 2;
4572 if (len)
4573 {
4574 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_length, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4575 offset += 2;
4576 }
4577 if (optlen == 0)
4578 {
4579 /* Don't complain about zero length if part of a config request - values will be assigned and included in the response message */
4580 if (!is_request) {
4581 expert_add_info(pinfo, cfg_attr_type_item, &ei_isakmp_attribute_value_empty);
4582 }
4583 return 2+len;
4584 }
4585 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_value, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4586 switch (cfg_attr_type) {
4587 case INTERNAL_IP4_ADDRESS1: /* 1 */
4588 if (optlen%4 == 0)
4589 {
4590 for (i = 0; i < optlen/4; i++)
4591 {
4592 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip4_address, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4593 offset += 4;
4594 }
4595 }
4596 break;
4597 case INTERNAL_IP4_NETMASK2: /* 2 */
4598 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip4_netmask, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4599 break;
4600 case INTERNAL_IP4_DNS3: /* 3 */
4601 if (optlen%4 == 0)
4602 {
4603 for (i = 0; i < optlen/4; i++)
4604 {
4605 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip4_dns, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4606 offset += 4;
4607 }
4608 }
4609 break;
4610 case INTERNAL_IP4_NBNS4: /* 4 */
4611 if (optlen%4 == 0)
4612 {
4613 for (i = 0; i < optlen/4; i++)
4614 {
4615 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip4_nbns, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4616 offset += 4;
4617 }
4618 }
4619 break;
4620 case INTERNAL_ADDRESS_EXPIRY5: /* 5 */
4621 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_address_expiry, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4622 break;
4623 case INTERNAL_IP4_DHCP6: /* 6 */
4624 if (optlen%4 == 0)
4625 {
4626 for (i = 0; i < optlen/4; i++)
4627 {
4628 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip4_dhcp, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4629 offset += 4;
4630 }
4631 }
4632 break;
4633 case APPLICATION_VERSION7: /* 7 */
4634 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_application_version, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4635 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4636 break;
4637 case INTERNAL_IP6_ADDRESS8: /* 8 */
4638 if (optlen%17 == 0)
4639 {
4640 for (i = 0; i < optlen/17; i++)
4641 {
4642 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_address_ip, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4643 offset += 16;
4644 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_address_prefix, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4645 offset += 1;
4646 }
4647 }
4648 break;
4649 case INTERNAL_IP6_NETMASK9: /* 9 Only in IKEv1 */
4650 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_netmask, tvb, offset, 18, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4651 break;
4652 case INTERNAL_IP6_DNS10: /* 10 */
4653 if (optlen%16 == 0)
4654 {
4655 for (i = 0; i < optlen/16; i++)
4656 {
4657 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_dns, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4658 offset += 16;
4659 }
4660 }
4661 break;
4662 case INTERNAL_IP6_NBNS11: /* 11 */
4663 if (optlen%16 == 0)
4664 {
4665 for (i = 0; i < optlen/16; i++)
4666 {
4667 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_nbns, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4668 offset += 16;
4669 }
4670 }
4671 break;
4672 case INTERNAL_IP6_DHCP12: /* 12 */
4673 if (optlen%16 == 0)
4674 {
4675 for (i = 0; i < optlen/16; i++)
4676 {
4677 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_dhcp, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4678 offset += 16;
4679 }
4680 }
4681 break;
4682 case INTERNAL_IP4_SUBNET13: /* 13 */
4683 if (optlen%8 == 0)
4684 {
4685 for (i = 0; i < optlen/8; i++)
4686 {
4687 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip4_subnet_ip, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4688 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip4_subnet_netmask, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4689 offset += 8;
4690 }
4691 }
4692 break;
4693 case SUPPORTED_ATTRIBUTES14: /* 14 */
4694 if (optlen%2 == 0)
4695 {
4696 for (i = 0; i < optlen/2; i++)
4697 {
4698 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_supported_attributes, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4699 offset += 2;
4700 }
4701 }
4702 break;
4703 case INTERNAL_IP6_SUBNET15: /* 15 */
4704 if (optlen%17 == 0)
4705 {
4706 for (i = 0; i < optlen/17; i++)
4707 {
4708 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_subnet_ip, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4709 offset += 16;
4710 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_subnet_prefix, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4711 offset += 1;
4712 }
4713 }
4714 break;
4715 case INTERNAL_IP6_LINK17: /* 17 */
4716 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_link_interface, tvb, offset, 8, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4717 offset += 8;
4718 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_link_id, tvb, offset, optlen-8, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4719 break;
4720 case INTERNAL_IP6_PREFIX18: /* 18 */
4721 if (optlen%17 == 0)
4722 {
4723 for (i = 0; i < optlen/17; i++)
4724 {
4725 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_prefix_ip, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4726 offset += 16;
4727 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_internal_ip6_prefix_length, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4728 offset += 1;
4729 }
4730 }
4731 break;
4732 case P_CSCF_IP4_ADDRESS20: /* 20 */
4733 if (optlen%4 == 0)
4734 {
4735 for (i = 0; i < optlen/4; i++)
4736 {
4737 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_p_cscf_ip4_address, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4738 offset += 4;
4739 }
4740 }
4741 break;
4742 case P_CSCF_IP6_ADDRESS21: /* 21 */
4743 if (optlen%16 == 0)
4744 {
4745 for (i = 0; i < optlen/16; i++)
4746 {
4747 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_p_cscf_ip6_address, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4748 offset += 16;
4749 }
4750 }
4751 break;
4752 case XAUTH_TYPE16520: /* 16520 */
4753 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_type, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4754 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", rval_to_str(tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset), cfgattr_xauth_type, "Unknown %d"));
4755 break;
4756 case XAUTH_USER_NAME16521: /* 16521 */
4757 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_user_name, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4758 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4759 break;
4760 case XAUTH_USER_PASSWORD16522: /* 16522 */
4761 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_user_password, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4762 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4763 break;
4764 case XAUTH_PASSCODE16523: /* 16523 */
4765 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_passcode, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4766 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4767 break;
4768 case XAUTH_MESSAGE16524: /* 16524 */
4769 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_message, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4770 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4771 break;
4772 case XAUTH_CHALLENGE16525: /* 16525 */
4773 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_challenge, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4774 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4775 break;
4776 case XAUTH_DOMAIN16526: /* 16526 */
4777 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_domain, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4778 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4779 break;
4780 case XAUTH_STATUS16527: /* 16527 */
4781 proto_tree_add_item(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_status, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4782 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", val_to_str(tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset), cfgattr_xauth_status, "Unknown %d"));
4783 break;
4784 case XAUTH_NEXT_PIN16528: /* 16528 */
4785 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_next_pin, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4786 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4787 break;
4788 case XAUTH_ANSWER16529: /* 16527 */
4789 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_xauth_answer, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4790 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4791 break;
4792
4793 case UNITY_BANNER28672: /* 28672 */
4794 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_unity_banner, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4795 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4796 break;
4797 case UNITY_DEF_DOMAIN28674: /* 28674 */
4798 proto_tree_add_item_ret_string(sub_cfg_attr_type_tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_attr_unity_def_domain, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_ASCII0x00000000|ENC_NA0x00000000, wmem_packet_scope(), &str);
4799 proto_item_append_text(cfg_attr_type_item," : %s", str);
4800 break;
4801/* TODO: Support other UNITY Attributes ! */
4802 default:
4803 /* No Default Action */
4804 break;
4805 }
4806
4807 return 2+len+optlen;
4808}
4809
4810static void
4811dissect_config(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree, int isakmp_version, gboolean is_request)
4812{
4813 int offset_end = 0;
4814 offset_end = offset + length;
4815 if (isakmp_version == 1) {
4816
4817 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_type_v1,tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4818 offset += 2;
4819
4820 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_identifier, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4821 offset += 2;
4822
4823 } else if (isakmp_version == 2) {
4824
4825 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_cfg_type_v2,tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4826 offset += 4;
4827
4828 }
4829
4830 while (offset < offset_end) {
4831 offset += dissect_config_attribute(tvb, pinfo, tree, offset, isakmp_version, is_request);
4832 }
4833}
4834
4835static void
4836dissect_nat_discovery(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree )
4837{
4838 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_nat_hash, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4839}
4840
4841static void
4842dissect_nat_original_address(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, int length _U___attribute__((unused)), proto_tree *tree, int isakmp_version)
4843{
4844 guint8 id_type;
4845
4846 id_type = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4847 if (isakmp_version == 1)
4848 {
4849 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_id_type_v1, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4850 }else if (isakmp_version == 2)
4851 {
4852 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_id_type_v2, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4853 }
4854 offset += 1;
4855
4856 offset += 3; /* reserved */
4857
4858 switch (id_type) {
4859
4860 case IKE_ID_IPV4_ADDR1:
4861 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_nat_original_address_ipv4, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4862 break;
4863
4864 case IKE_ID_IPV6_ADDR5:
4865 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_nat_original_address_ipv6, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4866 break;
4867
4868 default:
4869 break;
4870 }
4871}
4872
4873static void
4874dissect_ts(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree)
4875{
4876 guint8 num, tstype, protocol_id;
4877
4878 num = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4879 proto_item_append_text(tree," # %d", num);
4880 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_number_of_ts, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4881
4882 offset += 1;
4883 length -= 1;
4884
4885 offset += 3; /* Reserved */
4886 length -= 3;
4887
4888 while (length > 0) {
4889 tstype = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4890 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_type, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4891
4892 offset += 1;
4893 length -= 1;
4894 switch (tstype) {
4895 case IKEV2_TS_IPV4_ADDR_RANGE7:
4896 protocol_id = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4897 if (protocol_id == 0)
4898 proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_protoid, tvb, offset,1,
4899 protocol_id, "Unused");
4900 else
4901 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_protoid, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4902 offset += 1;
4903 length -= 1;
4904
4905 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_selector_length, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4906 offset += 2;
4907 length -= 2;
4908
4909 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_start_port, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4910 offset += 2;
4911 length -= 2;
4912
4913 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_end_port, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4914 offset += 2;
4915 length -= 2;
4916
4917 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_start_addr_ipv4, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4918 offset += 4;
4919 length -= 4;
4920 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_end_addr_ipv4, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4921 offset += 4;
4922 length -= 4;
4923 break;
4924 case IKEV2_TS_IPV6_ADDR_RANGE8:
4925 protocol_id = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
4926 if (protocol_id == 0)
4927 proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_protoid, tvb, offset,1,
4928 protocol_id, "Unused");
4929 else
4930 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_protoid, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4931 offset += 1;
4932 length -= 1;
4933
4934 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_selector_length, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4935 offset += 2;
4936 length -= 2;
4937
4938 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_start_port, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4939 offset += 2;
4940 length -= 2;
4941
4942 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_end_port, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4943 offset += 2;
4944 length -= 2;
4945
4946 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_start_addr_ipv6, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4947 offset += 16;
4948 length -= 16;
4949
4950 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_end_addr_ipv6, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4951 offset += 16;
4952 length -= 16;
4953 break;
4954
4955 case IKEV2_TS_FC_ADDR_RANGE9:
4956 offset += 1; /* Reserved */
4957 length -= 1;
4958
4959 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_selector_length, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4960 offset += 2;
4961 length -= 2;
4962
4963 offset += 1; /* Reserved */
4964 length -= 1;
4965
4966 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_start_addr_fc, tvb, offset, 3, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4967 offset += 3;
4968 length -= 3;
4969
4970 offset += 1; /* Reserved */
4971 length -= 1;
4972
4973 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_end_addr_fc, tvb, offset, 3, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4974 offset += 3;
4975 length -= 3;
4976
4977 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_start_r_ctl, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4978 offset += 1;
4979 length -= 1;
4980
4981 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_end_r_ctl, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4982 offset += 1;
4983 length -= 1;
4984
4985 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_start_type, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4986 offset += 1;
4987 length -= 1;
4988
4989 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_end_type, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4990 offset += 1;
4991 length -= 1;
4992 break;
4993 default:
4994 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_ts_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4995 offset += length;
4996 length -= length;
4997 break;
4998 }
4999 }
5000}
5001
5002/* For IKEv2, decrypt payload if necessary and dissect using inner_payload */
5003/* For RFC 7383 reassembly, only need decrypted payload, so don't set dissect_payload_now .*/
5004/* TODO: rename? */
5005static tvbuff_t*
5006dissect_enc(tvbuff_t *tvb,
5007 int offset,
5008 int length,
5009 proto_tree *tree,
5010#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5011 packet_info *pinfo,
5012 guint8 inner_payload,
5013 gboolean is_request,
5014 void* decr_info,
5015 gboolean dissect_payload_now)
5016#else
5017 packet_info *pinfo _U___attribute__((unused)),
5018 guint8 inner_payload _U___attribute__((unused)),
5019 gboolean is_request _U___attribute__((unused)),
5020 void* decr_info _U___attribute__((unused)),
5021 gboolean dissect_payload_now _U___attribute__((unused)))
5022#endif
5023{
5024#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5025 ikev2_decrypt_data_t *key_info = NULL((void*)0);
5026 gint iv_len, encr_data_len, icd_len, decr_data_len, md_len;
5027 guint8 pad_len;
5028 guchar *iv = NULL((void*)0), *encr_data = NULL((void*)0), *decr_data = NULL((void*)0), *entire_message = NULL((void*)0), *md = NULL((void*)0);
5029 gcry_cipher_hd_t cipher_hd;
5030 gcry_md_hd_t md_hd;
5031 gcry_error_t err = 0;
5032 proto_item *item = NULL((void*)0), *icd_item = NULL((void*)0), *encr_data_item = NULL((void*)0), *padlen_item = NULL((void*)0), *iv_item = NULL((void*)0);
5033 tvbuff_t *decr_tvb = NULL((void*)0);
5034 gint payloads_len;
5035 proto_tree *decr_tree = NULL((void*)0), *decr_payloads_tree = NULL((void*)0);
5036
5037 if (decr_info) {
5038 /* Need decryption details to know field lengths. */
5039 key_info = (ikev2_decrypt_data_t*)(decr_info);
5040 iv_len = key_info->encr_spec->iv_len;
5041 icd_len = key_info->auth_spec->trunc_len;
5042 encr_data_len = length - iv_len - icd_len;
5043
5044 /*
5045 * Zero or negative length of encrypted data shows that the user specified
5046 * wrong encryption algorithm and/or authentication algorithm.
5047 */
5048 if (encr_data_len <= 0) {
5049 proto_tree_add_expert(tree, pinfo, &ei_isakmp_enc_iv, tvb, offset, length);
5050 return NULL((void*)0);
5051 }
5052
5053 /*
5054 * Add the IV to the tree and store it in a packet scope buffer for later decryption
5055 * if the specified encryption algorithm uses IV.
5056 */
5057 if (iv_len) {
5058 if (dissect_payload_now) {
5059 iv_item = proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_enc_iv, tvb, offset, iv_len, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5060 proto_item_append_text(iv_item, " (%d bytes)", iv_len);
5061 }
5062 iv = (guchar *)tvb_memdup(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, offset, iv_len);
5063
5064 offset += iv_len;
5065 }
5066
5067 /*
5068 * Add the encrypted portion to the tree and store it in a packet scope buffer for later decryption.
5069 */
5070 if (dissect_payload_now) {
5071 encr_data_item = proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_enc_data, tvb, offset, encr_data_len, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5072 proto_item_append_text(encr_data_item, " (%d bytes)",encr_data_len);
5073 }
5074 encr_data = (guchar *)tvb_memdup(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, offset, encr_data_len);
5075 offset += encr_data_len;
5076
5077 /*
5078 * Add the ICD (Integrity Checksum Data) to the tree before decryption to ensure
5079 * the ICD be displayed even if the decryption fails.
5080 */
5081 if (icd_len) {
5082 icd_item = proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_enc_icd, tvb, offset, icd_len, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5083 proto_item_append_text(icd_item, " (%d bytes)",icd_len);
5084
5085 /*
5086 * Recalculate ICD value if the specified authentication algorithm allows it.
5087 */
5088 if (key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg) {
5089 err = gcry_md_open(&md_hd, key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->auth_spec->gcry_flag);
5090 if (err) {
5091 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(),proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %d: gcry_md_open failed: %s"
, key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg, gcry_strerror(err)))
5092 "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %d: gcry_md_open failed: %s",proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %d: gcry_md_open failed: %s"
, key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg, gcry_strerror(err)))
5093 key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg, gcry_strerror(err)))proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %d: gcry_md_open failed: %s"
, key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg, gcry_strerror(err)));
5094 }
5095 err = gcry_md_setkey(md_hd, key_info->auth_key, key_info->auth_spec->key_len);
5096 if (err) {
5097 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(),proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %s, key length %u: gcry_md_setkey failed: %s"
, gcry_md_algo_name(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg), key_info
->auth_spec->key_len, gcry_strerror(err)))
5098 "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %s, key length %u: gcry_md_setkey failed: %s",proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %s, key length %u: gcry_md_setkey failed: %s"
, gcry_md_algo_name(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg), key_info
->auth_spec->key_len, gcry_strerror(err)))
5099 gcry_md_algo_name(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg), key_info->auth_spec->key_len, gcry_strerror(err)))proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %s, key length %u: gcry_md_setkey failed: %s"
, gcry_md_algo_name(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg), key_info
->auth_spec->key_len, gcry_strerror(err)));
5100 }
5101
5102 /* Calculate hash over the bytes from the beginning of the ISAKMP header to the right before the ICD. */
5103 entire_message = (guchar *)tvb_memdup(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, 0, offset);
5104 gcry_md_write(md_hd, entire_message, offset);
5105 md = gcry_md_read(md_hd, 0);
5106 md_len = gcry_md_get_algo_dlen(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg);
5107 if (md_len < icd_len) {
5108 gcry_md_close(md_hd);
5109 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(),proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %s: gcry_md_get_algo_dlen returned %d which is smaller than icd length %d"
, gcry_md_algo_name(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg), md_len
, icd_len))
5110 "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %s: gcry_md_get_algo_dlen returned %d which is smaller than icd length %d",proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %s: gcry_md_get_algo_dlen returned %d which is smaller than icd length %d"
, gcry_md_algo_name(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg), md_len
, icd_len))
5111 gcry_md_algo_name(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg), md_len, icd_len))proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 hashing error: algorithm %s: gcry_md_get_algo_dlen returned %d which is smaller than icd length %d"
, gcry_md_algo_name(key_info->auth_spec->gcry_alg), md_len
, icd_len));
5112 }
5113 if (tvb_memeql(tvb, offset, md, icd_len) == 0) {
5114 proto_item_append_text(icd_item, "[correct]");
5115 } else {
5116 proto_item_append_text(icd_item, "[incorrect, should be %s]", bytes_to_str(wmem_packet_scope(), md, icd_len));
5117 expert_add_info(pinfo, icd_item, &ei_isakmp_ikev2_integrity_checksum);
5118 }
5119 gcry_md_close(md_hd);
5120 } else {
5121 proto_item_append_text(icd_item, "[not validated]");
5122 }
5123 }
5124
5125 /*
5126 * Confirm encrypted data length is multiple of block size.
5127 */
5128 if (encr_data_len % key_info->encr_spec->block_len != 0) {
5129 proto_item_append_text(encr_data_item, "[Invalid length, should be a multiple of block size (%u)]",
5130 key_info->encr_spec->block_len);
5131 expert_add_info(pinfo, encr_data_item, &ei_isakmp_enc_data_length_mult_block_size);
5132 return NULL((void*)0);
5133 }
5134
5135 /*
5136 * Allocate buffer for decrypted data.
5137 */
5138 decr_data = (guchar*)wmem_alloc(pinfo->pool, encr_data_len);
5139 decr_data_len = encr_data_len;
5140
5141 /*
5142 * If the cipher is NULL, just copy the encrypted data to the decrypted data buffer.
5143 * And otherwise perform decryption with libgcrypt.
5144 */
5145 if (key_info->encr_spec->number == IKEV2_ENCR_NULL1) {
5146 memcpy(decr_data, encr_data, decr_data_len);
5147 } else {
5148 err = gcry_cipher_open(&cipher_hd, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_mode, 0);
5149 if (err) {
5150 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(),proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, mode %d: gcry_cipher_open failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec
->gcry_mode, gcry_strerror(err)))
5151 "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, mode %d: gcry_cipher_open failed: %s",proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, mode %d: gcry_cipher_open failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec
->gcry_mode, gcry_strerror(err)))
5152 key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_mode, gcry_strerror(err)))proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, mode %d: gcry_cipher_open failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec
->gcry_mode, gcry_strerror(err)));
5153 }
5154 err = gcry_cipher_setkey(cipher_hd, key_info->encr_key, key_info->encr_spec->key_len);
5155 if (err) {
5156 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(),proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, key length %d: gcry_cipher_setkey failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec
->key_len, gcry_strerror(err)))
5157 "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, key length %d: gcry_cipher_setkey failed: %s",proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, key length %d: gcry_cipher_setkey failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec
->key_len, gcry_strerror(err)))
5158 key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec->key_len, gcry_strerror(err)))proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, key length %d: gcry_cipher_setkey failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, key_info->encr_spec
->key_len, gcry_strerror(err)));
5159 }
5160 err = gcry_cipher_setiv(cipher_hd, iv, iv_len);
5161 if (err) {
5162 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(),proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, iv length %d: gcry_cipher_setiv failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, iv_len, gcry_strerror(
err)))
5163 "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, iv length %d: gcry_cipher_setiv failed: %s",proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, iv length %d: gcry_cipher_setiv failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, iv_len, gcry_strerror(
err)))
5164 key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, iv_len, gcry_strerror(err)))proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d, iv length %d: gcry_cipher_setiv failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, iv_len, gcry_strerror(
err)));
5165 }
5166 err = gcry_cipher_decrypt(cipher_hd, decr_data, decr_data_len, encr_data, encr_data_len);
5167 if (err) {
5168 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(),proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d: gcry_cipher_decrypt failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, gcry_strerror(err)))
5169 "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d: gcry_cipher_decrypt failed: %s",proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d: gcry_cipher_decrypt failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, gcry_strerror(err)))
5170 key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, gcry_strerror(err)))proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "IKEv2 decryption error: algorithm %d: gcry_cipher_decrypt failed: %s"
, key_info->encr_spec->gcry_alg, gcry_strerror(err)));
5171 }
5172 gcry_cipher_close(cipher_hd);
5173 }
5174
5175 decr_tvb = tvb_new_child_real_data(tvb, decr_data, decr_data_len, decr_data_len);
5176 add_new_data_source(pinfo, decr_tvb, "Decrypted Data");
5177 item = proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_enc_decrypted_data, decr_tvb, 0, decr_data_len, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5178 proto_item_append_text(item, " (%d byte%s)", decr_data_len, plurality(decr_data_len, "", "s")((decr_data_len) == 1 ? ("") : ("s")));
5179
5180 /* Move the ICD item to the bottom of the tree. */
5181 if (icd_item) {
5182 proto_tree_move_item(tree, item, icd_item);
5183 }
5184 decr_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(item, ett_isakmp_decrypted_data);
5185
5186 pad_len = tvb_get_guint8(decr_tvb, decr_data_len - 1);
5187 payloads_len = decr_data_len - 1 - pad_len;
5188
5189 if (payloads_len > 0) {
5190 item = proto_tree_add_item(decr_tree, hf_isakmp_enc_contained_data, decr_tvb, 0, payloads_len, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5191 proto_item_append_text(item, " (%d byte%s)", payloads_len, plurality(payloads_len, "", "s")((payloads_len) == 1 ? ("") : ("s")));
5192 decr_payloads_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(item, ett_isakmp_decrypted_payloads);
5193 }
5194
5195 padlen_item = proto_tree_add_item(decr_tree, hf_isakmp_enc_pad_length, decr_tvb, payloads_len + pad_len, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
5196 if (pad_len > 0) {
5197 if (payloads_len < 0) {
5198 proto_item_append_text(padlen_item, " [too long]");
5199 expert_add_info(pinfo, padlen_item, &ei_isakmp_enc_pad_length_big);
5200 } else {
5201 item = proto_tree_add_item(decr_tree, hf_isakmp_enc_padding, decr_tvb, payloads_len, pad_len, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5202 proto_item_append_text(item, " (%d byte%s)", pad_len, plurality(pad_len, "", "s")((pad_len) == 1 ? ("") : ("s")));
5203 proto_tree_move_item(decr_tree, item, padlen_item);
5204 }
5205 }
5206
5207 /*
5208 * We dissect the inner payloads at last in order to ensure displaying Padding, Pad Length and ICD
5209 * even if the dissection fails. This may occur when the user specify wrong encryption key.
5210 */
5211 if (dissect_payload_now && decr_payloads_tree) {
5212 dissect_payloads(decr_tvb, decr_payloads_tree, 2, inner_payload, 0, payloads_len, pinfo, 0, is_request, decr_info);
5213 }
5214 }else{
5215#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */
5216 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_enc_iv, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5217 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_enc_data, tvb, offset+4 , length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5218#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5219 }
5220 return decr_tvb;
5221#else /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */
5222 return NULL((void*)0);
5223#endif
5224}
5225
5226static void
5227dissect_eap(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree, packet_info *pinfo)
5228{
5229 tvbuff_t *eap_tvb;
5230
5231 eap_tvb = tvb_new_subset_length(tvb, offset, length);
5232 if ((eap_tvb != NULL((void*)0))&& eap_handle != NULL((void*)0)){
5233 call_dissector(eap_handle, eap_tvb, pinfo, tree);
5234 }else{
5235 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_eap_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5236 }
5237}
5238
5239static void
5240dissect_gspm(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, int length, proto_tree *tree)
5241{
5242 proto_tree_add_item(tree, hf_isakmp_gspm_data, tvb, offset, length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5243
5244}
5245
5246/*
5247 * Protocol initialization
5248 */
5249
5250#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5251static guint
5252isakmp_hash_func(gconstpointer c) {
5253 const guint8 *i_cookie = (const guint8 *) c;
5254 guint val = 0, keychunk, i;
5255
5256 /* XOR our icookie down to the size of a guint */
5257 for (i = 0; i < COOKIE_SIZE8 - (COOKIE_SIZE8 % (guint)sizeof(keychunk)); i += (guint)sizeof(keychunk)) {
5258 memcpy(&keychunk, &i_cookie[i], sizeof(keychunk));
5259 val ^= keychunk;
5260 }
5261
5262 return val;
5263}
5264
5265static gint
5266isakmp_equal_func(gconstpointer ic1, gconstpointer ic2) {
5267
5268 if (memcmp(ic1, ic2, COOKIE_SIZE8) == 0)
5269 return 1;
5270
5271 return 0;
5272}
5273
5274static guint ikev2_key_hash_func(gconstpointer k) {
5275 const ikev2_uat_data_key_t *key = (const ikev2_uat_data_key_t*)k;
5276 guint hash, *key_segs;
5277 size_t key_segcount, i;
5278
5279 hash = 0;
5280
5281 /*
5282 * XOR our icookie down to the size of a guint.
5283 *
5284 * The cast to guint suppresses a warning 64-bit-to-32-bit narrowing
5285 * from some buggy C compilers (I'm looking at *you*,
5286 * i686-apple-darwin11-llvm-gcc-4.2 (GCC) 4.2.1
5287 * (Based on Apple Inc. build 5658) (LLVM build 2336.11.00).)
5288 */
5289 key_segcount = key->spii_len / (guint)sizeof(guint);
5290 key_segs = (guint *)key->spii;
5291 for (i = 0; i < key_segcount; i++) {
5292 hash ^= key_segs[i];
5293 }
5294 key_segcount = key->spir_len / (guint)sizeof(guint);
5295 key_segs = (guint *)key->spir;
5296 for (i = 0; i < key_segcount; i++) {
5297 hash ^= key_segs[i];
5298 }
5299
5300 return hash;
5301}
5302
5303static gint ikev2_key_equal_func(gconstpointer k1, gconstpointer k2) {
5304 const ikev2_uat_data_key_t *key1 = (const ikev2_uat_data_key_t *)k1;
5305 const ikev2_uat_data_key_t *key2 = (const ikev2_uat_data_key_t *)k2;
5306 if (key1->spii_len != key2->spii_len) return 0;
5307 if (key1->spir_len != key2->spir_len) return 0;
5308 if (memcmp(key1->spii, key2->spii, key1->spii_len) != 0) return 0;
5309 if (memcmp(key1->spir, key2->spir, key1->spir_len) != 0) return 0;
5310
5311 return 1;
5312}
5313#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */
5314
5315#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5316static void
5317free_cookie_key(gpointer key_arg)
5318{
5319 guint8 *ic_key = (guint8 *)key_arg;
5320
5321 g_slice_free1(COOKIE_SIZE8, ic_key);
5322}
5323
5324static void
5325free_cookie_value(gpointer value)
5326{
5327 decrypt_data_t *decr = (decrypt_data_t *)value;
5328
5329 g_hash_table_destroy(decr->iv_hash);
5330 g_slice_free1(sizeof(decrypt_data_t), decr);
5331}
5332#endif
5333
5334static void
5335isakmp_init_protocol(void) {
5336#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5337 guint i;
5338 decrypt_data_t *decr;
5339 guint8 *ic_key;
5340#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */
5341 reassembly_table_init(&isakmp_cisco_reassembly_table,
5342 &addresses_reassembly_table_functions);
5343 reassembly_table_init(&isakmp_ike2_reassembly_table,
5344 &addresses_reassembly_table_functions);
5345
5346#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5347 isakmp_hash = g_hash_table_new_full(isakmp_hash_func, isakmp_equal_func,
5348 free_cookie_key, free_cookie_value);
5349
5350 for (i = 0; i < num_ikev1_uat_data; i++) {
5351 ic_key = (guint8 *)g_slice_alloc(COOKIE_SIZE8);
5352 memcpy(ic_key, ikev1_uat_data[i].icookie, COOKIE_SIZE8);
5353
5354 decr = create_decrypt_data();
5355 memcpy(decr->secret, ikev1_uat_data[i].key, ikev1_uat_data[i].key_len);
5356 decr->secret_len = ikev1_uat_data[i].key_len;
5357
5358 g_hash_table_insert(isakmp_hash, ic_key, decr);
5359 }
5360 ikev2_key_hash = g_hash_table_new(ikev2_key_hash_func, ikev2_key_equal_func);
5361 for (i = 0; i < num_ikev2_uat_data; i++) {
5362 g_hash_table_insert(ikev2_key_hash, &(ikev2_uat_data[i].key), &(ikev2_uat_data[i]));
5363 /* Need find references to algorithms (as UAT table editing looses data not stored in file) */
5364 ikev2_uat_data[i].encr_spec = ikev2_decrypt_find_encr_spec(ikev2_uat_data[i].encr_alg);
5365 ikev2_uat_data[i].auth_spec = ikev2_decrypt_find_auth_spec(ikev2_uat_data[i].auth_alg);
5366 }
5367 defrag_next_payload_hash = g_hash_table_new(g_direct_hash, g_direct_equal);
5368#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */
5369}
5370
5371static void
5372isakmp_cleanup_protocol(void) {
5373 reassembly_table_destroy(&isakmp_cisco_reassembly_table);
5374 reassembly_table_destroy(&isakmp_ike2_reassembly_table);
5375#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5376 g_hash_table_destroy(isakmp_hash);
5377 g_hash_table_destroy(ikev2_key_hash);
5378 g_hash_table_destroy(defrag_next_payload_hash);
5379#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */
5380}
5381
5382#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
5383static void
5384isakmp_prefs_apply_cb(void) {
5385 isakmp_cleanup_protocol();
5386 isakmp_init_protocol();
5387}
5388#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */

5390#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1

5394
5395static gboolean ikev1_uat_data_update_cb(void* p, char** err) {
5396 ikev1_uat_data_key_t *ud = (ikev1_uat_data_key_t *)p;
5397
5398 if (ud->icookie_len != COOKIE_SIZE8) {
5399 *err = g_strdup_printf("Length of Initiator's COOKIE must be %d octets (%d hex characters).", COOKIE_SIZE8, COOKIE_SIZE8 * 2);
5400 return FALSE(0);
5401 }
5402
5403 if (ud->key_len == 0) {
5404 *err = g_strdup("Must have Encryption key.");
5405 return FALSE(0);
5406 }
5407
5408 if (ud->key_len > MAX_KEY_SIZE256) {
5409 *err = g_strdup_printf("Length of Encryption key limited to %d octets (%d hex characters).", MAX_KEY_SIZE256, MAX_KEY_SIZE256 * 2);
5410 return FALSE(0);
5411 }
5412
5413 return TRUE(!(0));
5414}

5424
5425static gboolean ikev2_uat_data_update_cb(void* p, char** err) {
5426 ikev2_uat_data_t *ud = (ikev2_uat_data_t *)p;
5427
5428 if (ud->key.spii_len != COOKIE_SIZE8) {
5429 *err = g_strdup_printf("Length of Initiator's SPI must be %d octets (%d hex characters).", COOKIE_SIZE8, COOKIE_SIZE8 * 2);
5430 return FALSE(0);
5431 }
5432
5433 if (ud->key.spir_len != COOKIE_SIZE8) {
5434 *err = g_strdup_printf("Length of Responder's SPI must be %d octets (%d hex characters).", COOKIE_SIZE8, COOKIE_SIZE8 * 2);
5435 return FALSE(0);
5436 }
5437
5438 if ((ud->encr_spec = ikev2_decrypt_find_encr_spec(ud->encr_alg)) == NULL((void*)0)) {
5439 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG("Couldn't get IKEv2 encryption algorithm spec.")proto_report_dissector_bug("Couldn't get IKEv2 encryption algorithm spec."
);
5440 }
5441
5442 if ((ud->auth_spec = ikev2_decrypt_find_auth_spec(ud->auth_alg)) == NULL((void*)0)) {
5443 REPORT_DISSECTOR_BUG("Couldn't get IKEv2 authentication algorithm spec.")proto_report_dissector_bug("Couldn't get IKEv2 authentication algorithm spec."
);
5444 }
5445
5446 if (ud->sk_ei_len != ud->encr_spec->key_len) {
5447 *err = g_strdup_printf("Length of SK_ei (%u octets) does not match the key length (%u octets) of the selected encryption algorithm.",
5448 ud->sk_ei_len, ud->encr_spec->key_len);
5449 return FALSE(0);
5450 }
5451
5452 if (ud->sk_er_len != ud->encr_spec->key_len) {
5453 *err = g_strdup_printf("Length of SK_er (%u octets) does not match the key length (%u octets) of the selected encryption algorithm.",
5454 ud->sk_er_len, ud->encr_spec->key_len);
5455 return FALSE(0);
5456 }
5457
5458 if (ud->sk_ai_len != ud->auth_spec->key_len) {
5459 *err = g_strdup_printf("Length of SK_ai (%u octets) does not match the key length (%u octets) of the selected integrity algorithm.",
5460 ud->sk_ai_len, ud->auth_spec->key_len);
5461 return FALSE(0);
5462 }
5463
5464 if (ud->sk_ar_len != ud->auth_spec->key_len) {
5465 *err = g_strdup_printf("Length of SK_ar (%u octets) does not match the key length (%u octets) of the selected integrity algorithm.",
5466 ud->sk_ar_len, ud->auth_spec->key_len);
5467 return FALSE(0);
5468 }
5469
5470 return TRUE(!(0));
5471}
5472#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */

6640 proto_isakmp = proto_register_protocol("Internet Security Association and Key Management Protocol",
6641 "ISAKMP", "isakmp");
6642 proto_register_field_array(proto_isakmp, hf, array_length(hf)(sizeof hf / sizeof hf[0]));
6643 proto_register_subtree_array(ett, array_length(ett)(sizeof ett / sizeof ett[0]));
6644 expert_isakmp = expert_register_protocol(proto_isakmp);
6645 expert_register_field_array(expert_isakmp, ei, array_length(ei)(sizeof ei / sizeof ei[0]));
6646 register_init_routine(&isakmp_init_protocol);
6647 register_cleanup_routine(&isakmp_cleanup_protocol);
6648
6649 register_dissector("isakmp", dissect_isakmp, proto_isakmp);
6650
6651#ifdef HAVE_LIBGCRYPT1
6652 isakmp_module = prefs_register_protocol(proto_isakmp, isakmp_prefs_apply_cb);
6653 ikev1_uat = uat_new("IKEv1 Decryption Table",
6654 sizeof(ikev1_uat_data_key_t),
6655 "ikev1_decryption_table",
6656 TRUE(!(0)),
6657 &ikev1_uat_data,
6658 &num_ikev1_uat_data,
6659 UAT_AFFECTS_DISSECTION0x00000001, /* affects dissection of packets, but not set of named fields */
6660 "ChIKEv1DecryptionSection",

6662 ikev1_uat_data_update_cb,
6663 NULL((void*)0),
6664 NULL((void*)0),
6665 ikev1_uat_flds);
6666
6667 prefs_register_uat_preference(isakmp_module,
6668 "ikev1_decryption_table",
6669 "IKEv1 Decryption Table",
6670 "Table of IKE_SA security parameters for decryption of IKEv1 packets",
6671 ikev1_uat);
6672
6673 ikev2_uat = uat_new("IKEv2 Decryption Table",
6674 sizeof(ikev2_uat_data_t),
6675 "ikev2_decryption_table",
6676 TRUE(!(0)),
6677 &ikev2_uat_data,
6678 &num_ikev2_uat_data,
6679 UAT_AFFECTS_DISSECTION0x00000001, /* affects dissection of packets, but not set of named fields */
6680 "ChIKEv2DecryptionSection",
6681 NULL((void*)0),
6682 ikev2_uat_data_update_cb,
6683 NULL((void*)0),
6684 NULL((void*)0),
6685 ikev2_uat_flds);
6686
6687 prefs_register_uat_preference(isakmp_module,
6688 "ikev2_decryption_table",
6689 "IKEv2 Decryption Table",
6690 "Table of IKE_SA security parameters for decryption of IKEv2 packets",
6691 ikev2_uat);
6692
6693#endif /* HAVE_LIBGCRYPT */
6694}
6695
6696void
6697proto_reg_handoff_isakmp(void)
6698{
6699 dissector_handle_t isakmp_handle;
6700
6701 isakmp_handle = find_dissector("isakmp");
6702 eap_handle = find_dissector_add_dependency("eap", proto_isakmp);
6703 dissector_add_uint("udp.port", UDP_PORT_ISAKMP500, isakmp_handle);
6704 dissector_add_uint("tcp.port", TCP_PORT_ISAKMP500, isakmp_handle);
6705}
